# Storm's Beacon
---
Display: Storms Beacon
---
Prof. Storm has a lead on the Beacon - an ancient signal buried in the ruins the old
giants left behind. A small ship, a long quiet run, and something already hunting the
same trail.

## Scenario
---
Mode: story
---
// Mode: story = a single-ship narrative with the Admiral economy OFF (no ## Admiralty
// or ## Worldlets chapter). This mission loads only the universe_core mastlib, so the
// admiral addon is not even present - admiralty_active() is False throughout.

## Narrative

### Storm's Lead (beacon_1)
---
Scope: shared
State: active
When: reach 2, -1
Then: reveal beacon_2
---
Prof. Storm's voice crackles over comms: the Beacon's carrier tone folds into an
eleven-hundred-year-old Torgoth channel, bearing coreward past the old marches to
(2, -1). "That is where they were biggest," she says. "Before they shrank. Before they
left the big empty houses behind." Bring the ship about and jump.

### The Giant's House (beacon_2)
---
Scope: shared
State: secret
When: scan 1 derelict
Pays: 200 credits
---
It hangs in the dark far larger than anything that flies today - a Torgoth megastation
from the age when the Torgoth themselves were giants, its docking throats wide enough to
swallow your ship whole. The Beacon's trail runs straight into it. Bring the science
array to bear and read what the ruin remembers.

## Goals

### Read the Ruin (goal_read_ruin)
---
Scope: shared
State: active
When: scan 1 derelict
Win: true
Citation: The megastation archive gave up the next bearing - and Prof. Storm has her trail again. The Beacon is still out there, and so is whoever is following the same clues.
---
Follow Storm's lead to (2, -1) and scan the Torgoth megastation to pull the Beacon's next
bearing from the ruin.

## Landmarks

### Torgoth Megastation (giants_house)
---
At: 2, -1
Kind: derelict
---
A derelict from the age of giants - a Torgoth station built to a scale no modern hull
needs, running dark for a thousand years, and still holding one faint echo of the Beacon
in its cold archive.
